This paper deals with natural language processing techniques applied to medical text, specifically the extraction of information from abstracts of articles related to randomised controlled trials. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses supervised classification techniques, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of support vector machines is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with medical text, which could also fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
